Many working people have rest at health resorts and holiday homes 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 30 (KCNA) -- At least 200,000 working people of Korea took a rest at health resorts and holiday homes at state expense this year.
 On January 3 this year, leader Kim Jong Il told officials to extensively build rest homes and health resorts for the people throughout the country.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Hundreds of health resorts and holiday homes have since been built or reconstructed on famous mountains, at scenic spots, on east and west sea beaches and at beauty places, where working people had a rest free of charge. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This demonstrates the true advantages and vitality of the socialist system.

Small groups of Pyongyang Circus perform abroad 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 30 (KCNA) -- Small groups of the Pyongyang Circus are proving successful in the international combined circus performances now underway in Stuttgart of Germany and Madrid and Valencia of Spain respectively.
 Korean acrobats staged acrobatic pieces "seesaw and swing", "trick on pole", "fliers", "ring turning" and "flying girls", etc. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 One of the organizers of the international combined circus performance in Stuttgart said after seeing the acrobatic pieces "seesaw and swing" and "trick on pole" that no country in this world can reach the level of Korean circus showing the national character peculiar to Korea and its flawless technique. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The chief in charge of the performances noted that "trick on pole" is the best in its skill and treble somersault backside is rare to be seen in any other countries.
 After watching the performance given by a small group of the Pyongyang Circus in Madrid, the mayor and other officials of the city praised "fliers" as the best masterpiece. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The general director of the circus theatre of Spain said that this number is an impeccable work which instills strength and courage into spectators and leads them to a fascinating world of fantasy and rich emotion with high acrobatic skill and elegant movement in the air. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, the acrobatic number "flying girls" is now being presented in Valencia. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The chief in charge of the performances at the Valencia theatre noted that this acrobatic number is one of the world's best numbers, adding the free flying of Korean girls in the air is something very mysterious.

Reception given by North Hamgyong Provincial People's Committee 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 30 (KCNA) -- The North Hamgyong Provincial People's Committee hosted a reception yesterday on the occasion of the New Year Juche 91 (2002).
 Present on invitation were consul general Liu Zhigang and staff members of the Chinese consulate general in Chongjin, consul general Arkadi Lavrov and staff members of the Russian consulate general in Chongjin. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were Kim Song Gwon, vice-chairman of the provincial people's committee, and other officials concerned. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speeches were made there.
